==English==

===Noun===
{{wikipedia2|hypocoristic}}
'''hypocorism'''

===Meaning===
#A form of [[endearment]]; a [[pet]] [[name]]
#The use of pet names

===Etymology===
Late Latin '''hypocorisma''', a loan from Greek noun υποκορισμα ('''hypokorisma''') from the verb υποκορι ('''hypokorizesthai''' = 'to call by pet names'). The Greek verb ''hypokorizesthai'' is compounded from [[υπο]] ([[hypo-]] = 'under, beneath, secretly') + κορ (korizesthai = 'to [[caress]]'). In the verb you can see the word κορος (koros = '[[boy]]') or κορη (korè = '[[girl]]').

